Rott abraham de Bra
den ue van 27 deser ontfangen, d' oncost ick sal examiaeren
& ue ten eersten de rest remitteren het pack N. woort eerst heden

pack in aftraeren van Jan botter ingelaeden d'ingeslotenen gelieft
voortganckk te geven blijve

3 July
Londen M Sabberton
In answer to yours of 14 past, I returne you mee hartye thancks for the
speins you have been plases to take about my different with m. Vivran
hopeing, you will bee so hinde to see that ended for you are a persen sull
expedientie & there fore will referre my case holly to you & lett m. vivian de
the some, & the sedictts as to thoth the have taken, I shhall oblige my self
t6 comfirmit att anney time, or pleaded. wee are obliged by articles of agreem
to be are port of letters eith as the shall receaef them, besaith, no advantage
if one should more taken more painesthen thinother, butt by not article am
my obliged to pay all charges inflandres, nether in vivian in engelant for
the charges inflanders, a month to severall ƒ 1000, acso as they have
brought to accompt, in with accoumpt the ƒ 409„15 here omitted & according
to what the article as have obliged ince no port of letters brought in, neither
deddeting for as mouch I have are more troubled & pans then m
vivian & do I charges the cost of my voyages to brussel, I charges not for my
painse. m vivian as been once in the nord, & that the promised th to do, to his
cost & charges, now if he pleases I shall allowing may cheire indempt charges
if he will not lett you desade the bisnes, I am contented to khoyse an abstrator
& that he shall make choyce of an ather, butt pray lett mee havve can exccompt
first of hispretences drawen up in writinge & may doubt then monney so
os have then mine. for as long as he have lived, heard not accase to here
been given to arbitrage, without parties the liver over first one or an other

seeing positiviley, that he that will not give an accompt of his pretences
before the arbetrators here choyeed, as no minde to make ende, I am all
most achaimed to trouble you, must more an other freind, that as no
acquaintes of so sellie a differens therefore in fabberton I know, if no
